#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:34
msgid "Waveform and RGB Parade"
msgstr "Signalna oblika in Parada RGB"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:36
msgid ""
"**Waveform** and **RGB Parade** are two closely related scopes. They do the "
"same - Waveform for :term:`Luma`, RGB Parade for the :abbr:`RGB (Red Green "
"Blue)` components. Therefore, we will not always explicitly point out what "
"properties hold for both scopes and speak of Waveform only."
msgstr ""
"**Signnalna oblika** in **Parada RGB** sta tesno povezana merilnika. Njuna "
"naloga je enaka - Signalna oblika za :term:`lumo<Luma>`, Parada RGB za "
"komponente :abbr:`RGB (angl. Red Green Blue)`. Zato ne bomo vedno izrecno "
"poudarjali, katere lastnosti veljajo za oba merilnika, in bomo govorili le o "
"merilniku Signalna oblika."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:44
msgid "Kdenlive Waveform :term:`widget`"
msgstr ":term:`Gradnik<widget>` Oblika signala Kdenlive"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:48
msgid "How the Waveform Works"
msgstr "Kako deluje signalna oblika"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:50
msgid ""
"The Waveform is kind of a 3D Histogram. That has nothing to do with the fact "
"that the above image looks kind of 3D. So where are the three dimensions?"
msgstr ""
"Signalna oblika je nekakšen 3D-histogram. To nima nobene zveze z dejstvom, "
"da je zgornja slika videti nekako 3D. Kje so torej tri dimenzije?"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:52
msgid ""
"The most obvious dimension is :term:`Luma`: Dark pixels are at the bottom, "
"bright ones are at the top. So if all pixels in the Waveform stick at the "
"very top, your video is most likely white."
msgstr ""
"Najbolj očitna mera je :term:`Luma`; temne slikovne točke so na dnu, svetle "
"so na vrhu. Če torej vse slikovne točke v signalni obliki ostajajo na vrhu, "
"je vaš video najverjetneje bel."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:54
msgid ""
"The second dimension is the horizontal position of the pixel in the original "
"image. That is one of the things that makes the Waveform cool. Pixels in the "
"first column of your input video will also be painted in the first column of "
"the Waveform. This goes on until the scope reaches the last column of the "
"input video, which will be painted in the last column of the Waveform."
msgstr ""
"Druga dimenzija je vodoravni položaj slikovne točke v prvotni sliki. To je "
"ena od stvari, zaradi katere je Signalna oblika kul. Slikovne točke v prvem "
"stolpcu vhodnega videa bodo pobarvane tudi v prvem stolpcu Signalne oblike. "
"To se nadaljuje, dokler merilnik ne doseže zadnjega stolpca vhodnega videa, "
"ki bo pobarvan v zadnjem stolpcu Signalne oblike."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:56
msgid ""
"The third dimension is the brightness of a pixel in the Waveform. The "
"brighter a point there, the more pixels in this column share this specific "
"brightness value."
msgstr ""
"Tretja dimenzija je svetlost slikovne točke v Signalni obliki. Svetlejša ko "
"je točka tam, več slikovnih točk v tem stolpcu deli to določeno vrednost "
"svetlosti."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:59
msgid "Waveform Example 1: Sunset"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 1: sončni zahod"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:67
msgid "Waveform example 1"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 1"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:69
msgid ""
"The Waveform looks quite impressive here. But what can we learn about the "
"image?"
msgstr ""
"Signalna oblika je videti zelo impresivno. Kaj pa lahko izvemo o podobi?"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:71
msgid ""
"In the left third we have got some clipping. There are some bright spots "
"which are the sun and the clouds."
msgstr ""
"V levi tretjini imamo nekaj porezave. Obstaja nekaj svetlih lis, ki "
"predstavljajo sonce in oblake."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:73
msgid ""
"The last third of the image is dark, but not black (no crushing). This means "
"that there is still a chance for color information. The image confirms that: "
"The tree does not look neutral but green with an orange touch. Or is it the "
"other way round?"
msgstr ""
"Zadnja tretjina slike je temna, ne pa črna (brez zlivanja). To pomeni, da še "
"vedno obstaja možnost za barvne informacije. Slika to potrjuje; drevo ni "
"videti nevtralno, ampak zeleno z oranžnim odtenkom. Ali pa je ravno obratno?"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:75
msgid "That is where the RGB Parade drops in now."
msgstr "Tu je zdaj naloga za parado RGB."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:83
msgid "Kdenlive RGB Parade :term:`widget`"
msgstr ":term:`<Gradnik>widget` Parada RGB Kdenlive"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:85
msgid ""
"What we see is very slight crushing for blue on the tree, and more or less "
"equal parts of red and green as well. So if you thought the tree were green, "
"your brain fooled you. It is not. (Actually there is no green at all in the "
"image.) Also, blue nearly does not clip at all, even in the sun. So it is "
"still a little bit orange, which is great."
msgstr ""
"Kar vidimo, je zelo rahlo stapljanje modre na drevesu, in prav tako bolj ali "
"manj enaki deli rdeče in zelene. Če ste mislili, da je drevo zeleno, so vas "
"možgani prevarali. Ni (pravzaprav na sliki sploh ni zelene barve). Tudi "
"modra se skoraj sploh ne poreže, niti na soncu. Torej je še vedno malce "
"oranžna, kar je super."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:87
msgid ""
"Now, did the Histogram not show clipping and crushing as well? Yes, it did. "
"But it did not show where. That is a big benefit. As in some cases, if you "
"see that there is some clipping on a light bulb, you perhaps do not mind "
"increasing the overall brightness of the image. It does increase clipping as "
"seen on the Histogram, but the Waveform shows that only the light bulb is "
"clipped a little more, which you can afford in our imaginary case."
msgstr ""
"Ni histogram pokazal tudi porezave in stapljanja? Da, res je. Vendar ni "
"pokazal, kje. To je velika korist. Kot v nekaterih primerih, če vidite, da "
"je nekaj porezano na žarnici, morda ne moti povečati splošne svetlosti "
"slike. To res poveča izrez na histogramu, vendar signalna oblika kaže, da je "
"samo žarnica porezana malce več, kar si v našem namišljenem primeru lahko "
"privoščite."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:90
msgid "RGB Parade Example: Light Bulb"
msgstr "Primer parade RGB: žarnica"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:92
msgid ""
"Wait … imaginary? Actually there is a short clip with light bulbs. Which is "
"quite interesting, not only due to the wrong white balance. See the how-to "
"guide :doc:`/tips_and_tricks/how-tos/tutorial-white_balance_lms` for more "
"details about white balance and how to use it in Kdenlive."
msgstr ""
"Čakajte … namišljenem? Pravzaprav obstaja kratek posnetek z žarnicami. Ki je "
"precej zanimiv, ne le zaradi napačne beline. Za več podrobnosti o ravnovesju "
"beline in njegovi uporabi v programu Kdenlive glejte priročnik :doc:`/"
"tips_and_tricks/how-tos/tutorial-white_balance_lms`."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:100
msgid "RGB Parade example 1"
msgstr "Primer parade RGB 1"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:102
msgid ""
"The RGB Parade reveals two things at first glance. You will at least "
"recognize the first one as well."
msgstr ""
"Parada RGB na prvi pogled razkriva dve stvari. Vsaj prvp boste prepoznali."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:104
msgid ""
"The fluorescent lamps are clipped. All channels are at 255 there, so they "
"are totally white."
msgstr ""
"Fluorescenčne svetilke so porezane. Vsi kanali so tam na 255, tako da so "
"popolnoma beli."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:106
msgid ""
"The white balance is wrong. This can be told for sure. The ceiling is white "
"in reality. And the left-most quarter of the image consists exclusively of "
"the ceiling. This part should look equal in the RGB Parade, but when e.g. "
"comparing Red to Blue, you see that Red starts at 19 whereas Blue starts at "
"0. Furthermore, the Blue channel is much more compressed. Its height in this "
"area is 25, whereas the height of the Red channel is about 50."
msgstr ""
"Izravnava beline je napačna. To lahko zagotovo ugotovite. Strop je v resnici "
"bel. Levo četrtino slike tvori izključno strop. Ta del bi moral biti v "
"Paradi RGB videti enak, vendar ko npr. primerjate rdečo in modro barvo, "
"vidite, da se rdeča začne pri 19, medtem ko se modra začne pri 0. Poleg tega "
"je modri kanal veliko bolj stisnjen. Njegova višina na tem območju je 25, "
"medtem ko je višina rdečega kanala približno 50."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:108
msgid ""
"To achieve proper white balance here we make use of a new effect called :ref:"
"`SOP/Sat <effects-sop_sat>`. :ref:`Curves <effects-curves>` would work as "
"well (actually curves could do everything), but let's use a new effect here."
msgstr ""
"Da bi dosegli ustrezno ravnovesje beline, uporabimo nov učinek z imenom :ref:"
"`SOP/Sat <effects-sop_sat>`. :ref:`Krivulje <effects-curves>` bi prav tako "
"delovale (pravzaprav bi krivulje lahko naredile vse), vendar tukaj uporabimo "
"nov učinek."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:110
msgid ""
"The first thing to decide is how bright the darkest spot should be. This can "
"be controlled with the :guilabel:`Offset` parameter. Reference is again the "
"left part of the Parades, the soon-to-be white ceiling. You can use your "
"mouse to make the Waveform or RGB Parade draw a horizontal line and display "
"the value there. All channels were lifted to around 50 in this example:"
msgstr ""
"Najprej se odločite, kako svetla naj bo najtemnejša točka. To je mogoče "
"nadzorovati s parametrom :guilabel:`Zamik`. Referenca je spet levi del "
"parade, kmalu beli strop. Z miško lahko poskrbite, da Signalna oblika ali "
"Parada RGB nariše vodoravno črto in tam prikaže vrednost. V tem primeru so "
"bili vsi kanali dvignjeni na približno 50:"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:112
msgid ""
"The :ref:`effects-sop_sat` uses a different scale than the RGP Parade :term:"
"`widget`. The lifting of the channels refers to the RGB Parade scale "
"(0...255) as one can see in the :guilabel:`Min` in the RGB Parade display. "
"The idea is to lift the channels so that there bottoms are aligned."
msgstr ""
"Pri :ref:`effects-sop_sat` se uporablja drugačno merilo kot pri :term:"
"`gradniku<widget>` Parada RGB. Dvigovanje kanalov se nanaša na lestvico "
"Parade RGB (0…255), kot je razvidno iz :guilabel:`Min` v prikazu Parade RGB. "
"Ideja je dvigniti kanale tako, da so njihova dna poravnana."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:120
msgid "Using the :ref:`effects-sop_sat` to change the color tone"
msgstr "Uporaba učinka :ref:`effects-sop_sat` za spremembo barvnega tona"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:122
msgid ""
"Second step is stretching the channels. This is done with the :guilabel:"
"`Slope` sliders. The goal is again to find a neutral spot in the RGB Parade "
"and use it as reference. We could again use the ceiling on the left, but "
"after some testing it turned out that the little wave in the middle of the "
"scope works as well. Its advantage is that it is slightly brighter than the "
"ceiling allowing to correct the color cast more precisely."
msgstr ""
"Drugi korak je raztezanje kanalov. To opravimo z drsniki :guilabel:`Naklon`. "
"Cilj je ponovno najti nevtralno točko v Paradi RGB in jo uporabiti kot "
"referenco. Spet bi lahko uporabili strop na levi, vendar smo po nekaterih "
"testiranjih ugotovil, da deluje tudi mali val sredi merilnika. Njegova "
"prednost je v tem, da je nekoliko svetlejša od stropa, kar omogoča, da bolj "
"natančno popravi obarvanost."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:130
msgid "Using the :ref:`effects-sop_sat` to adjust white balance"
msgstr ""
"Uporaba učinka :ref:`effects-sop_sat` za prilagoditev ravnovesja beline"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:132
msgid "And voilà, exposure and white balance are corrected."
msgstr "In voilà, ekspozicija in ravnovesje beline sta popravljeni."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:134
msgid ""
"When taking a look at the full-sized image (or when trying it yourself with "
"the sample clip available for download at the end of this article) you will "
"notice color waves in the image. This is the result of the stretching: We "
"have blown up the ceiling on the left from 25px height to nearly 100px. If "
"the clip had been exposured and white-balanced correctly when shooting, we "
"would have 100 distinct values there, but now there are only 25 different "
"blue levels causing these steps. Also in the histogram the image looks torn "
"apart. (Another reason might be the high compression of the Nikon D90 "
"clips.) This effect is called *Posterization*\\ [#f1]_."
msgstr ""
"Ko si ogledate sliko v polni velikosti (ali ko jo sami preizkusite z "
"vzorčnim posnetkom, ki je na voljo za prenos na koncu tega članka), boste na "
"sliki opazili barvne valove. To je posledica raztezanja: strop na levi "
"strani smo s 25 sl. točkami višine povečali na skoraj 100 sl. točk. Če bi "
"bil posnetek med snemanjem pravilno osvetljen in uravnotežene beline, bi tam "
"imeli 100 različnih vrednosti, zdaj pa je le 25 različnih ravni modre barve, "
"ki povzročajo te korake. Tudi v histogramu je slika videti raztrgana (še en "
"razlog je lahko velika stisnjenost posnetkov Nikon D90). Ta učinek se "
"imenuje *Posterizacija*\\ [#f1]_."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:136
msgid ""
"This is one of the reasons why more expensive cameras (and with that we mean "
"*really* expensive ones, like the *RED One*\\ [#f2]_, to name an extreme "
"example) record videos in higher bit depth\\ [#f3]_. Perhaps all clips you "
"will ever encounter only store 8 bits per channel, so there are 2\\ :sup:`8` "
"= 256 possible values for each channel. Having for example 10 bits per "
"channel would already result in 2\\ :sup:`10` = 1024 possible values. This "
"would already have solved our problem."
msgstr ""
"To je eden od razlogov, zakaj dražje kamere (s tem mislimo *resno* drage "
"fotoaparate, kot je *RED One*\\ [#f2]_, če omenimo skrajni primer) snemajo "
"videoposnetke z večjo bitno globino\\ [#f3]_. Morda vsi posnetki, s katerimi "
"se boste srečali, shranjujejo le 8 bitov na kanal, zato je za vsak kanal na "
"voljo 2\\ :sup:`8` = 256 možnih vrednosti. Če bi imeli na primer 10 bitov na "
"kanal, bi že dobili 2\\ :sup:`10` = 1024 možnih vrednosti. S tem bi bil naš "
"problem že rešen."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:138
msgid ""
"But before you buy a *RED One* now - Kdenlive does not support more than 8 "
"bit (yet)."
msgstr ""
"Ampak preden kupite kamero *RED one* zdaj – Kdenlive (še) ne podpira več kot "
"8 bitov."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:140
msgid ""
"Where you already can play with more than 8 bits per channel are :abbr:`RAW "
"(The RAW file format is digital photography's equivalent of a negative in "
"film photography: it contains untouched, raw pixel information straight from "
"the digital camera's sensor)` images from :abbr:`DSLR (DSLR stands for "
"Digital Single-Lens Reflex)` cameras. Supported by many image processing "
"applications such as |digikam| or |rawtherapee|."
msgstr ""
"Več kot 8 bitov na kanal lahko že uporabljate pri slikah :abbr:`RAW (format "
"datoteke RAW je v digitalni fotografiji je enakovreden negativu v filmski "
"fotografiji: vsebuje nedotaknjene, neobdelane informacije o slikovnih točkah "
"neposredno s tipala digitalnega fotoaparata ali kamere)` iz fotoaparatov :"
"abbr:`DSLR (DSLR je kratica za digitalni zrcalno-refleksni fotoaparat z enim "
"objektivom)`. Podpirajo ga številni programi za obdelavo slik, kot sta |"
"digikam| ali |rawtherapee|."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:143
msgid "Waveform Example 2: Leaf with Hidden Clipping"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 2: list s skrito porezavo"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:151
msgid "Waveform example 2"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 2"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:153
msgid ""
"Looks perfect. Good exposure (says the eye and the Waveform), beautiful "
"colors."
msgstr ""
"Videti je popolno. Dobra ekspozicija (pravi oko v signalni obliki), lepe "
"barve."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:155
msgid ""
"Nevertheless, there is some clipping. It is just hidden by the Luma "
"calculation: For Luma, only pixels that are totally white are at the top of "
"the Waveform."
msgstr ""
"Kljub temu je nekaj porezanosti. To je samo skrito z izračunom lume: Za lumo "
"so samo popolnoma bele slikovne točke na vrhu Signalne oblike."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:163
msgid "RGB Parade exposes clipping"
msgstr "Parada RGB razkrije porezavo"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:165
msgid ""
"Although the green leaf looks much brighter than the red tip, it is the Red "
"channel which clips at the tips. The thing is that our eyes are most "
"sensitive to Green, less to Red, and even less to Blue. That is also the "
"reason why the beam of a green laser is visible in the night sky, but a red "
"one is not - unless you've got a really strong one."
msgstr ""
"Čeprav je zeleni list videti veliko svetlejši od rdeče konice, je rdeči "
"kanal, ki je porezan na konicah. Stvar je v tem, da so naše oči najbolj "
"občutljive na zeleno, manj na rdečo, še manj pa na modro. To je tudi razlog, "
"zakaj je žarek zelenega laserja viden na nočnem nebu, rdeč pa ni (razen če "
"imate res močnega.)"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:168
msgid "Waveform Example 3: High Key Clip"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 3: posnetek z močnim glavnim virom osvetlitve"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:176
msgid "Waveform example 3"
msgstr "Primer signalne oblike 3"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:178
msgid ""
"This is a classical |high_key| shot. Bright subject (but not clipped yet), "
"white background."
msgstr ""
"To je klasičen posnetek s svetlimi toni (|high_key|). Svetel predmet (vendar "
"še ne porezan), belo ozadje."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:181
msgid "Waveform Options"
msgstr "Možnosti signalne oblike"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:183
msgid ""
"*Paint Mode* - Changes the paint mode for the Waveform. Usually changes its "
"brightness as well. Green also highlights pixels with values 0 or 255."
msgstr ""
"*Način slikanja* – spremeni način barve za Signalno obliko. Običajno "
"spremeni tudi svojo svetlost. Zelena osvetli tudi slikovne točke z "
"vrednostmi 0 ali 255."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:185
msgid ""
"*Luma mode* (Context menu) - As for the Histogram you can choose how to "
"calculate Luma (Rec.601 or Rec.709)."
msgstr ""
"*Način lume* (kontekstni meni) – kar zadeva histogram, lahko izberete, kako "
"izračunate lumo (Rec.601 ali Rec.709)."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:193
msgid "Waveform :term:`widget` with paint mode Green"
msgstr ":term:`Gradnik<widget>` Signalne oblike z načinom barvanja Zelena"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:195
msgid ""
"Interesting detail: When color grading, some colorists prefer scopes with "
"neutral colors and basically with neutral everything. Just greyscale except "
"for the video itself. Why is that? Quick answer and fun fact: |afterimages|. "
"If you look at a green surface and then immediately color grade an image by "
"eye, there will be too much green in it."
msgstr ""
"Zanimiva podrobnost: Pri razvrščanju barv imajo nekateri koloristi raje "
"merilnike z nevtralnimi barvami, in v bistvu vse z nevtralnim. Samo "
"sivinsko, razen samega videa. Zakaj je tako? Hiter odgovor: |popodobe|. Če "
"pogledate zeleno površino in nato takoj barvno korigirate sliko na oko, bo v "
"izdelku preveč zelene barve."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:198
msgid "RGB Parade Options"
msgstr "Možnosti Parade RGB"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:200
msgid "*Paint Mode* - Changes the paint mode; see above."
msgstr "*Način slikanja* – spremeni način slikanja; glejte zgoraj."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:202
msgid "*Draw Axis* (Context menu) - Draws an axis with 10 steps"
msgstr "*Nariši os* (kontekstni meni) – nariše os z 10 koraki"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:204
msgid ""
"*Gradient reference line* (Context menu) - Draws a line from bottom left to "
"top right. This is useful when testing color correction on a linear gradient "
"clip (Black on the left, White on the right), to observe changes in each "
"channels."
msgstr ""
"*Referenčna črta preliva* (kontekstni meni) – nariše črto od leve spodaj "
"proti desni zgoraj. To je uporabno pri preskušanju popravka barve na "
"linearnem prelivnem posnetku (črna na levi, bela na desni), za opazovanje "
"sprememb v posameznih kanalih."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:206
msgid ""
"To explain the last point a little more in detail: A black/white gradient "
"draws a line from the bottom left to top right on the Waveform. When "
"changing the colors, e.g. with the :ref:`SOP/Sat <effects-sop_sat>` effect "
"or with :ref:`Curves <effects-curves>`, the line will change."
msgstr ""
"Če želite podrobneje razložiti zadnjo reč: črno-beli preliv v Signalni "
"obliki nariše črto od levo spodaj proti desno zgoraj. Pri spreminjanju barv "
"npr. s filtrom :ref:`SOP/Sat <effects-sop_sat>` ali s :ref:`Krivuljami "
"<effects-curves>` se črta spremeni."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:208
msgid ""
"Effects working on the saturation will not have any effect on a grayscale "
"gradient!"
msgstr ""
"Učinki, ki delujejo na nasičenost, ne bodo vplivali na sivinski preliv!"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:216
msgid "Playing with the :ref:`effects-sop_sat` and a gradient"
msgstr "Igranje z :ref:`effects-sop_sat` in prelivom"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:218
msgid ""
"In this gradient above a :ref:`SOP/Sat <effects-sop_sat>` effect was applied "
"to give the blacks a blueish touch and the mids and highs a warm touch. You "
"can play around with the gradient file and some color correction effects on "
"the gradient file as well. What the above is good for will be in the next "
"part."
msgstr ""
"V tem prelivu zgoraj je uporabljen učinek SOP/Sat, da so črnine dobile "
"modrikast ton in srednje in visoke vrednosti topel občutek. Lahko se igrate "
"z datoteko preliva in nekaj učinki za popravek barve tudi na datoteki "
"preliva. Čemu je zgoraj navedeno namenjeno, bo sledilo v naslednjem delu."

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:222
msgid "Summary"
msgstr "Povzetek"

#: ../../tips_and_tricks/scopes/waveform_and_rgb_parade.rst:223
msgid ""
"**Waveform** and **RGB Parade** are powerful scopes. Especially the RGB "
"Parade. Correcting the exposure is easy, and with these scopes you can "
"always keep track of the levels of each color component. It is also possible "
"to do white balance by adjusting blacks first and whites afterwards because "
"the horizontal axis in the Scopes correspond to the horizontal axis in the "
"video which allows to detect spots that should be neutral."
msgstr ""
"**Signalna oblika** in **Parada RGB** so mogočni merilniki. Še posebej "
"Parada RGB. Popravljanje ekspozicije je enostavno, s temi merilniki lahko "
"vedno spremljate ravni vsake barvne komponente. Prav tako je mogoče narediti "
"ravnovesje beline s prilagajanjem najprej črnin in kasneje belin, ker "
"vodoravna os v merilnikih ustreza vodoravni osi v videu, ki omogoča "
"odkrivanje lis, ki bi morale biti nevtralne."

